<paragraph id="3588866466E54DA8811AFE8BBDE72975" pageId="0" pageNumber="103">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7F6683618E0444D569722DB55DD30DD3" pageId="0" pageNumber="103">
<taxonomicName id="F47C3EFC9F8E8ECAF03EA0B6D0B15DFB" authorityName="Torres-Garcia, Gene and Dania Garcia" authorityYear="2022" class="Eurotiomycetes" family="Aspergillaceae" genus="Penicillium" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Penicillium ausonanum" order="Eurotiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="103" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="ausonanum">
<emphasis id="7ECD18BFEFA763CF32820E06FE89B93D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="103">Penicillium ausonanum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
formed a phylogenetically supported group together with 
<taxonomicName id="352489476B8EAFAB6308FF57270AD469" genus="P." lsidName="P. amphipolaria" pageId="0" pageNumber="103" rank="species" species="amphipolaria">
<emphasis id="59B41B978A87BABC58226A62C7DB5090" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="103">P. amphipolaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="D58B2086638168FB2D7F2DC0A17ED500" genus="P." lsidName="P. viridissimum" pageId="0" pageNumber="103" rank="species" species="viridissimum">
<emphasis id="7EEAAABB5F6044C3F63F4D1F7AF94F2C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="103">P. viridissimum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in series 
<taxonomicName id="6D58D93AA44E23D2CFD3380C4D5AFFE4" genus="P." lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="103" rank="series" series="Dalearum">
<emphasis id="889AEF3D6F0CBE851CA5787FD21EBC0F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="103">Dalearum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="F51669E8D44CF6B172815BA04BBBF819" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Phylogenetic tree of Penicillium section Lanata-Divaricata based on ML analysis obtained by RAxML inferred from the combined tub 2, cmdA, ITS, and rpb 2 loci. Branch lengths are proportional to phylogenetic distance. Bootstrap support values / Bayesian posterior probability scores above 70 % / 0.95 are indicated on the nodes. Bold branches indicate bs / pp values 100 / 1. The tree is rooted to P. restrictum CBS 367.48 and P. corylophilum CBS 312.48. The name in red is the new species described in this study. T = Ex-type strain." figureDoi="10.3897/mycokeys.86.73861.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/640605" pageId="0" pageNumber="103">6</figureCitation>
). These are two species recently described, the former from soil in Antarctica and Canada, and the latter from acidic and forest soil from China (
<bibRefCitation id="1EA8D6A3ED19AD462C86D1F04B312A0A" DOI="https://doi.org/10.3767/003158516X691627" author="Visagie, CM" journalOrPublisher="Persoonia" pageId="0" pageNumber="103" pagination="247 - 280" refId="B90" refString="Visagie, CM, Renaud, JB, Burgess, KMN, Malloch, DW, Clark, D, Ketch, L, Urb, M, Louis-Seize, G, Assabgui, R, Sumarah, MW, Seifert, KA, 2016a. Fifteen new species of Penicillium. Persoonia 36: 247 - 280, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3767/003158516X691627" title="Fifteen new species of Penicillium." url="https://doi.org/10.3767/003158516X691627" volume="36" year="2016 a">Visagie et al. 2016a</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="0DE7BB96CEC5D0457721E9A0DB93BA90" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1111/cla.12365" author="Diao, YZ" journalOrPublisher="Cladistics" pageId="0" pageNumber="103" pagination="514 - 549" refId="B12" refString="Diao, YZ, Chen, Q, Jiang, XZ, Houbraken, J, Barbosa, RN, Cai, L, Wu, WP, 2019. Penicillium section Lanata-Divaricata from acidic soil. Cladistics 35: 514 - 549, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1111/cla.12365" title="Penicillium section Lanata-Divaricata from acidic soil." url="https://doi.org/10.1111/cla.12365" volume="35" year="2019">Diao et al. 2019</bibRefCitation>
). The new species can be morphologically differentiated from them by its equal proportion of monoverticillate and divaricate conidiophores, which are mostly with a complex branching pattern in 
<taxonomicName id="494ADAA4BF4409F146A1038FF37FD27C" genus="P." lsidName="P. amphipolaria" pageId="0" pageNumber="103" rank="species" species="amphipolaria">
<emphasis id="54C7F404725A10263C453CF6DB3E40FA" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="103">P. amphipolaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(biverticillate and divaricate) (
<bibRefCitation id="6D8ADCF1DC288C128AC2C6EF84636EEE" DOI="https://doi.org/10.3767/003158516X691627" author="Visagie, CM" journalOrPublisher="Persoonia" pageId="0" pageNumber="103" pagination="247 - 280" refId="B90" refString="Visagie, CM, Renaud, JB, Burgess, KMN, Malloch, DW, Clark, D, Ketch, L, Urb, M, Louis-Seize, G, Assabgui, R, Sumarah, MW, Seifert, KA, 2016a. Fifteen new species of Penicillium. Persoonia 36: 247 - 280, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3767/003158516X691627" title="Fifteen new species of Penicillium." url="https://doi.org/10.3767/003158516X691627" volume="36" year="2016 a">Visagie et al. 2016a</bibRefCitation>
), and mono- to terverticillate in 
<taxonomicName id="2D3767F398343CB5467D9BA3DC025244" genus="P." lsidName="P. viridissimum" pageId="0" pageNumber="103" rank="species" species="viridissimum">
<emphasis id="8748F7CAD4605534D28D7C41856E42EE" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="103">P. viridissimum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="CEC97E16E43701B166522A3E1713BAF0" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1111/cla.12365" author="Diao, YZ" journalOrPublisher="Cladistics" pageId="0" pageNumber="103" pagination="514 - 549" refId="B12" refString="Diao, YZ, Chen, Q, Jiang, XZ, Houbraken, J, Barbosa, RN, Cai, L, Wu, WP, 2019. Penicillium section Lanata-Divaricata from acidic soil. Cladistics 35: 514 - 549, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1111/cla.12365" title="Penicillium section Lanata-Divaricata from acidic soil." url="https://doi.org/10.1111/cla.12365" volume="35" year="2019">Diao et al. 2019</bibRefCitation>
). Both 
<taxonomicName id="1AB3EC42CC35383D81BFEDC0D1CBA2B2" genus="P." lsidName="P. amphipolaria" pageId="0" pageNumber="103" rank="species" species="amphipolaria">
<emphasis id="777958D2D1A28CB10C78AABAE3CC668F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="103">P. amphipolaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(6.5-10 
<normalizedToken id="62F30C3CDABCE7C19E36A468722FCAE0" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
) and 
<taxonomicName id="0E4204FEBF2ACA939F05A9018B21C0F1" genus="P." lsidName="P. viridissimum" pageId="0" pageNumber="103" rank="species" species="viridissimum">
<emphasis id="595CC0F1C9921DD7D3BEDF3DB73F62E2" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="103">P. viridissimum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(6.5-10 
<normalizedToken id="6503BA2B29EC32B523465D5EE65633C6" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
) have slightly shorter phialides than 
<taxonomicName id="212FF1C5D409D0A05F2B68C1CF70D349" genus="P." lsidName="P. ausonanum" pageId="0" pageNumber="103" rank="species" species="ausonanum">
<emphasis id="340ACD18FF0062EDD70F1FB0256AA6F2" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="103">P. ausonanum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(9-12 
<normalizedToken id="2B8A5C918594679D93395E99A1D4C12F" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
). Also, 
<taxonomicName id="A260B361606E3FB80AC09CB6FE99DDB8" genus="P." lsidName="P. amphipolaria" pageId="0" pageNumber="103" rank="species" species="amphipolaria">
<emphasis id="ADAC41E4C9CBE017829AA2DA1DF8B6C7" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="103">P. amphipolaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(240-460 
<normalizedToken id="F98DAFA1402D45B41B415FCA4DE95683" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
) and 
<taxonomicName id="E4E3432550F9ABF39A8CF0158323B7BD" genus="P." lsidName="P. viridissimum" pageId="0" pageNumber="103" rank="species" species="viridissimum">
<emphasis id="9CD3C07EB9E39F2073818624917B69A4" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="103">P. viridissimum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(40-125 
<normalizedToken id="AABF006DD77BE2CD0289E67DC6878128" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
) have longer stipes (
<bibRefCitation id="4CD0F05B777990C8605898F0E2C1D5F1" DOI="https://doi.org/10.3767/003158516X691627" author="Visagie, CM" journalOrPublisher="Persoonia" pageId="0" pageNumber="103" pagination="247 - 280" refId="B90" refString="Visagie, CM, Renaud, JB, Burgess, KMN, Malloch, DW, Clark, D, Ketch, L, Urb, M, Louis-Seize, G, Assabgui, R, Sumarah, MW, Seifert, KA, 2016a. Fifteen new species of Penicillium. Persoonia 36: 247 - 280, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3767/003158516X691627" title="Fifteen new species of Penicillium." url="https://doi.org/10.3767/003158516X691627" volume="36" year="2016 a">Visagie et al. 2016a</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EE8979E11DC5C8B56E5166295BD0CB7A" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1111/cla.12365" author="Diao, YZ" journalOrPublisher="Cladistics" pageId="0" pageNumber="103" pagination="514 - 549" refId="B12" refString="Diao, YZ, Chen, Q, Jiang, XZ, Houbraken, J, Barbosa, RN, Cai, L, Wu, WP, 2019. Penicillium section Lanata-Divaricata from acidic soil. Cladistics 35: 514 - 549, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1111/cla.12365" title="Penicillium section Lanata-Divaricata from acidic soil." url="https://doi.org/10.1111/cla.12365" volume="35" year="2019">Diao et al. 2019</bibRefCitation>
) in comparison to those of 
<taxonomicName id="0D12A12135B957686519EE3C4F30135A" genus="P." lsidName="P. ausonanum" pageId="0" pageNumber="103" rank="species" species="ausonanum">
<emphasis id="BF0E9F4B865D5FB21C9AC2AF3113BC69" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="103">P. ausonanum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(20-120 
<normalizedToken id="906DF21DBC2FCFEAD1861DD5D9D97B84" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
). Furthermore, the three species also differed in acid production on CREA, which is strong in 
<taxonomicName id="9717280F7EF344AF832A1D1F03097C95" genus="P." lsidName="P. ausonanum" pageId="0" pageNumber="103" rank="species" species="ausonanum">
<emphasis id="9C8F2F38EAF6E0BCE4A90AAFEDEA951A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="103">P. ausonanum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, moderate in 
<taxonomicName id="4E48AD2E2D4F5743253B8B90CBD16FB6" genus="P." lsidName="P. amphipolaria" pageId="0" pageNumber="103" rank="species" species="amphipolaria">
<emphasis id="B96DEE352685FB2A8C40B78598E1AEA4" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="103">P. amphipolaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and absent in the neighboring species 
<taxonomicName id="C759D1A94D7D4F02BFA9749C58DCFF4B" genus="P." lsidName="P. viridissimum" pageId="0" pageNumber="103" rank="species" species="viridissimum">
<emphasis id="A4232B7A25236AE1E8F6B511B16EFDF8" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="103">P. viridissimum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
